quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,"I do swear by this city [of Makkah] –"
  90,2,"and you are free of restriction [for a while] in this city –"
  90,3,and by every parent and offspring
  90,4,We have created man in hardship
  90,5,Does he think that none can ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says, “I have squandered enormous wealth!”"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have We not given him two eyes
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,"and shown him the two ways [of right and wrong]"
  90,11,Yet he did not make his way through the steep path
  90,12,and how do you know what the steep path is
  90,13,It is freeing a slave
  90,14,or giving food on a day of hunger
  90,15,to an orphan relative
  90,16,or to a needy person in misery
  90,17,"then [most importantly] to be one of those who believe and exhort one another to patience and exhort one another to compassion"
  90,18,Such are the people of the Right
  90,19,"As for those who reject Our signs, they are the people of the Left"
  90,20,who will be locked up in the Fire
  91,1,By the sun and its brightness
  91,2,and by the moon as it follows it
  91,3,and by the day as it displays it
  91,4,and by the night as it covers it
  91,5,and by the sky and how He made it
  91,6,and by the earth and how He spread it
  91,7,and by the soul and how He fashioned it
  91,8,"then inspired it [to know] its wickedness and righteousness"
  91,9,"Indeed, he who purifies his soul will attain success"
  91,10,and he who corrupts it will be doomed
  91,11,"Thamūd rejected [the messenger] because of their transgression"
  91,12,"when the most wretched among them rose [to kill the camel]"
  91,13,"Although the messenger of Allah warned them, “Hands off the she-camel of Allah and her drink!”"
  91,14,Yet they rejected him and hamstrung her. So their Lord destroyed them for their sin and leveled them to the ground
  91,15,And He has no fear of the consequences thereof
  92,1,By the night when it covers
  92,2,and by the day when it appears
  92,3,and by His creation of male and female
  92,4,surely your efforts are divergent
  92,5,As for the one who gives in charity and fears Allah
  92,6,and truly believes in the best reward
  92,7,We will make easy for him the way of salvation
  92,8,But as for the one who is miserly and deems himself self-sufficient
  92,9,and denies the best reward
  92,10,We will make easy for him the way of perdition
  92,11,"His wealth will be of no avail to him when he tumbles [into Hell]"
  92,12,"Indeed, it is upon Us to show the right way"
  92,13,and surely to Us belong the Hereafter and the present life
  92,14,So I warn you of a raging Fire
  92,15,none will enter it except the most wretched
  92,16,who denied and turned away
  92,17,But the most righteous will be saved from it
  92,18,who spends his wealth to purify himself
  92,19,not in return for someone’s favors
  92,20,"but to seek the pleasure of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,He will surely be well pleased
  93,1,By the morning brightness
  93,2,and by the night when it is still
  93,3,"your Lord has not forsaken you [O Prophet], nor does He hate you"
  93,4,the Hereafter is better for you than the present life
  93,5,and your Lord will certainly give you so much that you will be well pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan then take good care of you
  93,7,Did He not find you unguided then guide you
  93,8,Did He not find you in need then enrich you
  93,9,So do not mistreat the orphan
  93,10,nor repulse the beggar
  93,11,and proclaim the blessings of your Lord